Package de.kaleidox.crystalshard.util

Class DefaultEmbed

  • java.lang.Object
    • de.kaleidox.crystalshard.util.DefaultEmbed
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.function.Supplier<EmbedDraft>
    public class DefaultEmbed
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.function.Supplier<EmbedDraft>
    This class represents a default EmbedDraft. It is used to define a default EmbedDraft that will be used by methods like MessageReciever.sendMessage(Consumer), where no embed draft is specified but an embed modifier is.

      • getStatic

        public static EmbedDraft getStatic​(java.util.function.Consumer<Embed.Builder> defaultEmbedModifier)
        A static implementation of the get() method. This method will first check if the current thread is a ThreadPool.Worker thread, and if so, will get the Discord item the Worker belongs to. Throws an exception if invoked from a wrong context. This method must only be invoked from "bot-own" threads.
        Parameters:
        defaultEmbedModifier - A modifier to be run on the default embed.
        Returns:
        The default EmbedDraft according to the Discord instance that this Thread belongs to.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalCallerException - If the current thread does not belong to any Discord object.
        See Also:
        ThreadPool.isBotOwnThread()
